title: YouTube Research
body:
Hey people, 

Those of you who used to watch (English) YouTubers back in 2010 - 2013 when collabs were a common occurrence and short films were being made:

  • Where are you now?
  • What are you watching these days?
  • Do you still follow the same YouTubers?
  • If not, why?

I also used to be part of that community and am not anymore as I outgrew it, I now prefer gaming type videos. (Also there was a lot of problems that surfaced and everyone stepped back)

body:
Coachella

Auf dem Coachella-Festival waren sie, die beiden.

Alle Jahre wieder und nie der Musik wegen.

Es ist reine Image-Sache, wie bei allen YouTubern und Instagram-Drohnen.

Sie gehen dort hin, um Fotos von sich selbst zu machen.

Die sie dann werbewirksam ins Netz stellen.

In den Köpfen und in den Zwischenräumen gähnende Leere.

Markenklamotten für die semi-gay Modedeppen-Males.

Möchtegern-Hippie-Look für die Females, die alle die gleiche Frisur haben.

Sie fahren nach Vegas, Santa Monica, Palm Springs, dem Grand Canyon — um Fotos zu machen.

Sie fahren nach Dubai, Bali, Abu Dhabi, Kroatien, Italien — um Fotos zu machen.

body: Guess what!!! I officially started my YouTube channel! My first video is now up. Go check it out! Link in bio. First video is just an introduction to myself so you guys can get to know me. I’m really excited and super nervous to start this journey. I’m a little awkward in the first video but I promise it will get better. If you guys wanna keep up with when I post, hit that subscribe button and that red bell to turn your post notifications on. Also leave a comment on what kinda videos you wanna see. More are already in the works. Ahhh! I’m so excited, lmk what you think!
